post_text: School will be closed starting Monday, March 16 through April 3 as directed by Governor Dewine. Students in 3rd, 4th and 5th grade will be given a Chromebook tomorrow. Students that do not have internet at home, will be given a Hot Spot tomorrow. Students should bring home all their materials tomorrow. Kindergarten through 2nd grade will be given hard copies of school work. We will continue to update you over the next three weeks. Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time.

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time.

The Struthers Board of Education is seeking letters of interest and resumes from individuals interested in filling a vacant Board of Education seat.

Chester Leone, who was elected to the Struthers City School Board in November, opted not to take his elected seat.

Those interested in serving on the Struthers City School Board of Education should submit letters of interest and resumes to the Struthers City School District Superintendent by January 22nd. The office is located at 99 Euclid Avenue, Struthers, OH 44471.

The board will begin interviewing candidates soon and must name a replacement within 30 days of the resignation.

post_text:
Struthers City Schools is seeking a new head football coach. Coach Curt Kuntz has resigned on Monday, January 6th.

Coach Kuntz has been coaching the Wildcats Football Team since 2012. The Wildcats have made four playoff appearances under Kuntz and in 2016, his team won the AAC championship. His 53 wins rank him among the tops at Struthers, with the likes of Bob Commings, Pete Pirone, Sr. and Gary Zetts.

"We would like to thank Coach Kuntz for his dedication and commitment to our football program the last 8 years," said Pete Pirone Jr., Struthers City Schools Superintendent. "Curt has done a tremendous job leading our student-athletes on and off the field. Coach Kuntz has re-instilled in our team what it means to be a Wildcat football player."

Qualified coaching candidates interested in applying for the Struthers City Schools Head Football Coach position, can send their resume and cover letter to the Superintendent at 99 Euclid Avenue, Struthers, OH 44471.
